# santi.env — systemd EnvironmentFile for santi.service / santi-upgrade.service.
# Copy to /etc/santi/santi.env, fill in real values, `chmod 600`, own by santi.
# santi.toml stays secret-free (env:// refs resolve against these).

# --- provider secrets (only the selected provider's keys need to resolve) ---
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
# SILICONFLOW_API_KEY=

# --- the runtime's API bearer (all endpoints except /health) ---
# SANTI_API_KEY=

# --- self-upgrade (PHASE-07) ---
# The self-strand the "come look" record is seeded into on upgrade. Without it,
# the upgrade still completes but seeds no doorbell (report.seeded=false).
# SANTI_STRAND_ID=
# On rollback, the previous .deb to reinstall (else only the runtime is restored).
# SANTI_PREVIOUS_DEB=
# Graceful-shutdown drain budget (default 600); santi.service TimeoutStopSec must exceed it.
# SANTI_SHUTDOWN_GRACE_SECS=600
# Whole-upgrade timeout budget (default 600); santi-upgrade.service TimeoutStartSec must exceed it.
# SANTI_UPGRADE_TIMEOUT_SECS=600
